  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Objectives of the position</strong></p><p>We are seeking a detail-oriented and proactive Senior Accountant to join our Finance team. This role is responsible for managing the full spectrum of accounting activities, with a strong focus on month-end closing, general accounting, fixed assets, tax compliance, and process improvement. The ideal candidate is analytical, organized, and able to work independently within a fast-paced environment. </p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure a timely and accurate financial month end closing and reporting.</li><li>Prepare journal entries and reconciliations to ensure accuracy and compliance with accounting policies.</li><li>Manage day-to-day general accounting functions, including general ledger maintenance, fixed asset accounting, and staff expense claims</li><li>Maintain and update the fixed asset register, including additions, disposals, transfers, and depreciation.</li><li>Analyze fluctuations in key balance sheet and P&L accounts to ensure data accuracy and completeness</li><li>Prepare audit schedules and supporting documentation</li><li>Liaise with internal and external auditors to ensure smooth audit processes.</li><li>Support the preparation of corporate income tax, GST, and other statutory filings, including statutory surveys.</li><li>Actively seeking areas of improvement and introducing automation and other measures to improve process efficiency.</li><li>Any other adhoc duties assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Skills & Qualification:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Accounting or equivalent professional qualification.</li><li>Candidate with at least 8 years working experience in Financial Accounting.</li><li>High attention to detail, strong analytical skills, and a proactive work attitude.</li><li>Strong knowledge of IFRS/SFRS and financial reporting principles,</li><li>Good Knowledge of SAP-FICO would be highly preferred.</li><li>Experience in setting up Shared Service Centre is a plus.</li><li>Mature personality with excellent interpersonal and communication skills.</li><li>Ability to work independently with emphasis on accuracy and timeliness.</li></ul>",
